	<title>PHP Object Fields with Hyphens</title>

	<content type="xhtml">
	<div xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
		<p>
			Did you know that PHP object fields can have hyphens in them?  Well (if you said "no"), they can.  People sometimes come across these when using <a href="http://php.net/simplexml">SimpleXML</a> to parse an XML language with tags with hyphens in the name.
		</p>
		<p>
			Well, to access the fields with hyphens, you do something like...
		</p>
		<pre><code class="php">
$obj-&gt;{'field-with-a-hyphen'}
		</code></pre>
		<p>
			... and...
		</p>
		<pre><code class="php">
$obj-&gt;{'quote-source'}
		</code></pre>
		<p>
			... and...
		</p>
		<pre><code class="php">
$apple-&gt;{'yellow-banana'}-&gt;{'red-cherry'}
		</code></pre>

